{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "If a Prime Minister resigns a general election should be called",
        "additional_details": "In the last few years 3 Prime Ministers have resigned and their successors chosen by their party and it has been business as usual despite public apathy and anger.\r\nWhile I agree that a party is in the right to choose their own leader I believe that \"business as usual\" should only be the case if a Prime Minister resigns for health reasons.\r\nFor all other cases it is only right that the public choose whether they want a new leadership or not and not down to the current government.",
        "background": "In the case of a Prime Minister resigning, a general election should be called at the earliest opportunity after a new leader of the party is elected, to allow the general population to choose whether they still trust the current government or not.",
